M1rD1TrbXPsI5EllXTVqeXdN.text: This library lets you display a life indicator, score and timer easily. It also takes care of publishing your scores to the cloud.

VKluEiPQFFuvPzbrnlnXYSKz.text: Let's start by creating a board which we will use for the demo.

xXWEVEPIbFAlmzBTa2sr1EQP.text: Call the `initialize` action with your game board to initialize the library. This should be done once when setting up your game.

XlHioCdv13pz8wEq5x4VkBO4.text: Simply call `set score` to display a score on the top right corner of the board. You can use `score` to get back the current value of the score.

MJKx3SYxX2gLffNIsYDzmhG0.text: Use the `set life` action to display a life indicator on the top left corner of the board. You can use `life` to get back the current value of the life.

ODGW02dnBM3q4Lkr3VEGeV2L.text: You can also display a timer by calling `start timer`. You can use `current time` to get the seconds elapsed since the start of the timer.

q4iFQcPaIzQYckhp632KGcKK.text: Make sure to call `evolve` in the game loop. In this example, we use a `while` loop to simulate the game loop.

IRiM464ZzGTWkLVdXgtoGyqQ.text: Use the `post score` action to publish the current score to the cloud.

gvmnExE9gt4bVhAkGiFSWQBA.text: Adds the value to the current score.
